The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump at the White House welcoming the 2017 NASCAR Champion, Martin Truex Jr., and the Furniture Row Racing Team. Trump congratulates Truex Jr. on his championship win and praises the team's accomplishments. He also recognizes other members of Congress and the Chairman and CEO of NASCAR, Brian France. Trump highlights the team's motto of "Never give up" and commends their resilience after facing tragedy during the season. He also acknowledges Sherry Pollex, Truex Jr.'s partner, for her battle with ovarian cancer. Truex Jr. presents Trump with a special gift, a replica of the helmet he wore during the championship season. The remarks end with a photo opportunity with the team and crew members.